history.content: That is likely to be true starting in Fall 2016. Central campus and the new Student Information Systems Project has not yet clearly communicated with departments what exactly those changes will look like so we don't have any more information than an ability to almost confirm the rumors that you've heard.

children.subject: I spoke with an SIS team lead and there will be no changes to phases or unit maximums for the upcoming telebears cycle in April, though you will technically be registering with the new system; functionally, it should be the same for you.  It's possible that phases will be replaced with a different procedure in future terms, but what that will be is still very much in the exploration phase.  When there's more clarity, I'll be sure to update everyone.  Good question!

I think it's too early to know. Hypothetically speaking, there are many ways they might proceed.  They could emulate the functionality of phases with other appointments that are staggered, or they could have something like an open enrollment; it'll just depend on what the solution looks like.  Prior to our current policy, we still prioritized majors but non-majors could waitlist during Phase I.  In part, this was the rationale for moving to Phase 2 for non-majors in that they'd sit on the waitlist any way so it would be better for them to use their Phase I for other priorities.  We'll make sure to message when there's more clarity, so don't worry just yet!

Do you (the advisors who responded above) know how that would effect enrollment in CS classes, considering the fact that phase 2 right now distinguishes enrollment between declared CS majors and non-CS majors? Or is it too early to ask this question? Thanks.

history.content: I heard from the grapevine that there was a rumor of Phase 2 being removed in favor of an expanded Phase 1 + adjustment. Is this true?
history.subject: Telebears change?
